table concurrent_futures_extra144.ppe_shutdown_and_map:
  description: "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.shutdown and map qualname, doc, and code checks — shutdown.__qualname__.__eq__('ProcessPoolExecutor.shutdown')==True (len=28: 'ProcessPoolExecutor'=19+'.'=1+'shutdown'=8=28; tied with __init__ for longest qualname in this spec; 1 more than TPE.shutdown at 27); shutdown.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures.process')==True (len=26: same process module); shutdown.__doc__.__len__()==491 (same length as TPE.shutdown at 491: the shared Executor.shutdown doc); shutdown.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True ('self','wait'); shutdown.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3 ('self','wait','cancel_futures' — 2 params + 1 local; compare TPE.shutdown which has 5 co_varnames including 'work_item' and 't'); map.__qualname__.__eq__('ProcessPoolExecutor.map')==True (len=23: 'ProcessPoolExecutor'=19+'.'=1+'map'=3=23; unlike ThreadPoolExecutor.map which has qualname 'Executor.map' at len=12, PPE overrides map directly so the qualname uses the full class name); map.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures.process')==True (len=26: process module, not _base); map.__doc__.__len__()==1052 (11 chars shorter than TPE's inherited Executor.map doc at 1063 — PPE has a process-specific override); map.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True ('self','fn'); map.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==7 ('self','fn','timeout','chunksize','buffersize','iterables','results' — 2 params + 5 locals); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: cfppe_sm144

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
