  description: "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.map.__qualname__.__len__() == 23 — concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.map.__qualname__ is 'ProcessPoolExecutor.map' (23 chars: 'ProcessPoolExecutor'=19+'.'=1+'map'=3=23); this is the shortest method qualname in this spec but unlike ThreadPoolExecutor.map (qualname 'Executor.map' at len=12), PPE overrides map directly so the qualname uses the full ProcessPoolExecutor class name; map.__module__=='concurrent.futures.process' (len=26: the process module, not _base); map.__doc__.__len__()==1052 (PPE-specific map doc, 11 chars shorter than TPE's inherited Executor.map doc at 1063); NEW in extra144: first standalone ProcessPoolExecutor.map qualname length invariant; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
